
 Parameters between brackets [] are optional
 
 Usage:  s3 rm [-r] CONTENT

     -r         Recursive removal, files inside directories
     CONTENT    Path to S3 content to remove


 WARNING: 
 To delete everything from the base directory, pass a dot (.) 
 as the argument while on recursive mode
     
 ________________________________________________________

 
 Delete everything from the base directory
 s3 rm -r .

 Delete a file from the base directory
 s3 rm temporal.bin

 Delete a file from a specific directory
 s3 rm images/background.jpeg

 Delete a directory (will delete the 2020 directory)
 s3 rm -r backup/2020/
 
